Dialogue: 0,0:34:52.34,0:34:54.54,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,前往火星殖民地\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on their way to colonies on Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.59,0:34:58.38,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,遭遇了寻找外快的太空海盗的拦截\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are intercepted by space pirates looking for a quick payday.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.47,0:35:03.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,现在 在大气层里 飞机需要有升力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Today, in an atmosphere, planes need to generate lift,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.51,0:35:05.47,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是它们有机翼的原因所在\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is why they have wings.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.52,0:35:06.60,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为它们有了机翼\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because they have wings
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.64,0:35:08.81,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为你还想让飞行员保持清醒\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and because you also want to keep your pilots conscious,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.85,0:35:10.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以你就有了长距离的侧飞拐弯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you have long banking turns.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.81,0:35:14.98,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,太空中 你无需这么做\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In space, you don't need to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.02,0:35:16.32,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你可能会看到飞船在飞翔\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You might have a spacecraft flying along
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.36,0:35:19.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,简单转身 向身后的家伙开火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and simply turn around and shoot the guy behind him.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.74,0:35:24.57,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那些就是在你无需空气的情况下所能做到的事情\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Those are the kinds of things you can do when you don't require an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.83,0:35:28.25,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于海盗袭击补给船队\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}As the pirates attack the supply convoy,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.29,0:35:32.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,双方模样古怪的战机发生了短兵相接\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the odd-looking fighters on both sides face off.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.79,0:35:36.55,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或许最佳的就是立方体外装满推进器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Probably the best would be a cube covered with thrusters,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.59,0:35:38.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或小火箭 以及传感器\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or little rockets, and sensors.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.63,0:35:40.59,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,没有空气需要担心的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Doesn't have an atmosphere to worry about,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.63,0:35:42.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因而阻力不是问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so drag is not an issue.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.68,0:35:47.31,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过你想能看到360度 三维\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But you want to be able to see 360 degrees, 3-dimensionally,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.35,0:35:50.23,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能够向四面八方都能开火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and be able to fire in all of those directions.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.27,0:35:52.64,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那就是立方体了\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would be a cube.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.69,0:35:56.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于这些怪模怪样的飞船战斗在真空的太空中\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}With these strange-looking craft fighting in the vacuum of space,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.77,0:35:59.07,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,打斗的动作看上去也\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the movements of the fight will also 
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.07,0:36:01.90,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,与地球上的空战大不一样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}look much different than an aerial battle over Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.37,0:36:07.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们会看到更多的急拉动作\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We're going to have much more jerky motion,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.29,0:36:10.16,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们可以突然向左边开火\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where we're allowed to suddenly just shoot off to the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:10.20,0:36:13.46,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,突然向右边开火 同时保持前行\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suddenly shoot off to the right while keeping our forward motion.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:13.50,0:36:15.79,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,我们能够发动火箭任意制动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We can throw rockets on to randomly brake
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.84,0:36:18.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,无需担心掉在星球上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}without having to worry about crashing down to a planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.01,0:36:22.01,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就像我们在大气层里所担心的那样\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like you have to worry about within an atmosphere.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.22,0:36:26.93,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但没有了任何空气让飞船减速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But without any atmosphere to slow spacecraft down,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.97,0:36:29.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那达到了这般高速的太空空战会不会\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}could space dogfights reach such high speeds
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.93,0:36:33.19,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,让人类飞行员开始崩溃呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the human pilots would begin to fall apart?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.23,0:36:35.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,这就是伊利诺伊州齐格勒的尼古拉斯\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's what Nicholas B. from Zeigler, Illinois,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.90,0:36:37.36,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,向《宇宙》节目提出的问题\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}wanted to ask "The Universe."
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.40,0:36:39.04,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,他发来短信 -\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So he texted 
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.40,0:36:42.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,到了何种速度 人类的原子就会被拆散呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at what speed do human atoms start to brake down?
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.99,0:36:46.78,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,尼古拉斯 你的问题其实是共同关心的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Nicholas, your question actually is about a common,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.82,0:36:49.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,但又是可以理解的误解\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but very understandable misconception.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.33,0:36:52.37,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其实在任何速度下都是稳定的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It turns out that atoms are stable at any speed,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.41,0:36:55.83,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因为在它们自己的参照系里 它们是静止的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because in their own frame of reference, they're at rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:55.88,0:37:01.00,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过 人类会死于遭遇到持续的加速\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}However, humans die if they're subject to sustained accelerations
Dialogue: 0,0:37:01.05,0:37:03.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,一旦超过了10个G\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}greater than about 10 g.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.22,0:37:05.05,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此 我会说那就是在星际旅行时的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So I would say that's the practical limit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.09,0:37:07.76,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,加速度的实际极限\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for accelerations during interstellar travel,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.80,0:37:08.89,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}10G\N10g.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.97,0:37:13.06,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,不过茫茫太空中又何来重力呢\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But how could there be g-forces in the emptiness of space
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.10,0:37:15.73,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那里根本就几乎没有什么引力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where there's barely any gravity at all?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:15.77,0:37:18.94,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,那全是因为爱因斯坦的等效原理\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's all because of Albert Einstein's equivalence principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.98,0:37:22.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,其广义相对论的关键部分\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a key part of his Theory of General Relativity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.44,0:37:26.28,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,它规定重力和加速度是等价的 \N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It states that gravity and acceleration are equivalent,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.32,0:37:28.24,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,比如电梯加速上升\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like an elevator accelerating up,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.28,0:37:31.49,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会让乘客感觉到好像有额外的重力\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}making a passenger feel like there's additional gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.54,0:37:33.33,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,在把他们推向地面\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pushing them into the floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.63,0:37:40.42,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此如果你在太空中移动太快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So if you moved around too quickly in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.46,0:37:41.75,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你就会扭动很快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and you jerked real quick,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:41.80,0:37:45.17,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你的大脑就会在你的脑袋里移动飞快\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}your brain would move around inside your skull so quickly
Dialogue: 0,0:37:45.22,0:37:46.84,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,就会把你自己给干掉\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you could kill yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.88,0:37:50.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,因此你可能希望你的飞船里的导航系统\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so you might want the guidance system of your spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.18,0:37:52.85,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,能让你避开那种机动\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to keep you from making those types of maneuvers.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.39,0:38:01.02,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,或者未来的战略家可能会决定让飞行员完全脱离战斗\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or future strategists may decide to keep pilots out of the fight entirely.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.07,0:38:05.11,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,所以是否貌似太空中的无人驾驶的战争呢？\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So then what would a pilotless battle in space look like?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.87,0:38:13.87,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,由于太空空战的复杂性和危险性\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because of the complexities and dangers of dogfighting in space,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.91,0:38:18.12,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,飞行员有可能被完全排除在未来的太空战之外\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pilots may be left out of future space battles altogether.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.17,0:38:21.63,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,想象一下我们的海盗船 在未来200年后\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Imagine our pirate ship, 200 years in the future,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.67,0:38:23.96,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,试图截获补给船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}trying to take over the supply ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.01,0:38:28.13,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,此时所有的人都留在了两艘宇航母舰上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}while all of the people remained on the two main spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.18,0:38:33.14,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,假设你有一艘巨大的载人或有人驾驶的飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Assuming you had a large manned or piloted spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:38:33.18,0:38:37.48,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,而卷入战斗的是另一艘同样大小的飞船\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that was engaged in combat operations with another vehicle the same size,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.52,0:38:40.40,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你是不会为其发射战斗机的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you wouldn't launch fighters at it.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.44,0:38:44.15,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,你会扔下一些小小的太空雷\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You would throw some tiny space mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.19,0:38:46.69,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,机动飞船 手提箱般大小\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}maneuverable vehicle, the size of a suitcase
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.74,0:38:47.74,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会是隐形的\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that would be stealthy,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:47.78,0:38:49.99,*Default,NTP,0000,0000,0000,,会漂浮在敌方的飞船身上\N{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would float up to the enemy spacecraft,
